features: 𝐁𝐔𝐈𝐋𝐓 𝐓𝐎 𝐋𝐀𝐒𝐓: Our innovative Statik TSumoCharge 27W USB C to i-Product cable is almost indestructible. It is made from a new liquid silicone material which is surprisingly soft to the touch with built-in nylon wire to provide exceptional durability and flexibility to withstand more than 20,000 bending tests. Surely, this will help you save money on cables that wear out easily.

𝐂𝐇𝐀𝐑𝐆𝐄 𝐘𝐎𝐔𝐑 𝐃𝐄𝐕𝐈𝐂𝐄𝐒 𝐅𝐀𝐒𝐓𝐄𝐑: Our silicone charging cable is a USB C cable 27W with BlitzCharge technology for a super fast charging experience. It is a fast charge cable that also supports data transfer. It is a USBC cable and it is compatible with MacBook Pro, MacBook Air, and iPad Pro. TSumoCharge delivers up to 4x more power than traditional cables so you can quick charge your devices even while on-the-go.

𝐀𝐕𝐎𝐈𝐃 𝐓𝐀𝐍𝐆𝐋𝐄𝐃 𝐂𝐀𝐁𝐋𝐄𝐒: Our 2 meters long Statik TSumoCharge Type C charging cable is 6 feet long and is not only strong, and powerful, but also a tangle-free USB C 27 W cable. It comes with a leather cable wrap that helps you organize it. You can bend, twist, or flex it, and still remains tangle-free. This means neat and easy safekeeping even when your USB C cable is stuffed inside your bag, pocket, or even wrapped around your portable charger.

𝐒𝐔𝐏𝐏𝐎𝐑𝐓𝐒 𝐃𝐀𝐓𝐀 𝐓𝐑𝐀𝐍𝐒𝐅𝐄𝐑: Our TSumoCharge silicone wire cable is not only useful in quick charging your devices but also offers an uninterrupted and fast data transfer capability. This is made possible by adding a second wire that transfers data signals. The high speed USB C cable USB-C charging cable is great for transferring files between laptops and smartphones.

𝐏𝐑𝐎𝐓𝐄𝐂𝐓𝐒 𝐘𝐎𝐔𝐑 𝐄𝐗𝐏𝐄𝐍𝐒𝐈𝐕𝐄 𝐃𝐄𝐕𝐈𝐂𝐄𝐒: Our TSumoCharge USB type C cable has a built-in smart chip - E-Marker that not only carries its identifications but most importantly it is smartly capable of monitoring the charging status and regulating the flow of current properly to protect your devices from overcharging. A USB C fast charging cable USB C cable 6ft for all your needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The cable ends are large and easy to hold , the cable is thick and very flexible. They’re excellent for the fast charging blocks . A little bulky for carrying around, but excellent for a dedicated charging location.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nicely priced cable with a great feel
reviews.reviewText: I'm always on the look out for good quality USB-C cables, and this one certainly caught my eye. The silicone sleeve is really nice, and overall the cable has a great feel to it. It is nice and flexible, but doesn't feel fragile. The usb-c connectors are really nice. I included a shot so you can see how it stacks up compared to a more typical braided usb-c cable. The bright orange is nice too, as it stands out in situations like with a chair, where I might accidently run over other cables that blend in a little too much.It's been my go-to cable for charging my headphones. Because of the flexibility, it's the most comfortably to have plugged into my headphones while I'm actively wearing them. Starting to feel like I want to get a couple more though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Listing is misleading
reviews.reviewText: We all define “durable” using different metrics. Statements are made like “rated for 20,000 bends”. This may be one of if not “the” least durable wire I’ve ever owned. It separated at the wire plug junction within a month or 2 of buying it. I don’t use the cord in intense situations. It stays in my car and plugs to my phone which is cradled in a hand free holder. There is zero stress on the joint what so ever. Simply put. Just poor quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy like a guitar cable
reviews.reviewText: Heavy duty sold connection. Using in situation where it will get moved around a lot and think it will hold up better than most

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent cable until it stopped working
reviews.reviewText: This cable was the best cable I have ever used. The construction is top notch. The connectors at each end light up which is great showing you that it’s on and working.The body of the cable is soft silicone so it never kinks and stays limp. Heavy material feels great too. The connectors are “clicky” when plugged in, which is nice.Then this happened…suddenly, I needed to push down on the lightning connection in order for it to make a connection to my iPhone. Then it became a wiggle and a push down and up. Now I don’t use it. Afraid of a short. Too bad.

reviews.reviewTitle: Photos trompeuses et ne tient pas 100 W
reviews.reviewText: Première déception dès l'ouverture du colis : ce qui, sur les photos, a été maquillé pour ressembler à des prises en métal est en fait des prises en plastiques au moulage grossier. Le logo de la marque a même été gravé au laser après coup (car c'est probablement un "produit blanc") sauf que bien sûr, laser sur plastique égale traces de brûlé.J'ai acheté le cable spécifiquement pour un usage 100 W (donc 20 V / 5 A) : il "bugge". Je ne sais pas ce que c'est, mais soit les conducteurs sont trop fins pour 5 A, soit le module dans chaque prise qui sert à allumer une petite LED bleue perturbe le fonctionnement. Je n'ai même pas tenté de transférer des données avec.Je pense que ce câble est très pauvre en cuivre. On sent qu'il est très, très léger comparer simplement à des fils silicones vraiment taillés pour 5 A. Je vais probablement demander un retour.Je n'aurais même pas donné 3 euros pour un cable pareil. On dirait une merde Tému : joli de loin, mais aussi solide qu'un Kleenex mouillé. Oh et la lanière en cuir (si c'est est) est tellement fine que je pourrais la déchirer sans forcer.
